HEADWORD: Braunite
<hw>Braun"ite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A native oxide of manganese, of dark brownish black color. It was
named from a Mr. <etsep>Braun</etsep> of Gotha.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

